ns1:ModoOperacionCancelChannelSync a ns1:ModoOperacion ;
    rdfs:label "Cancel channel synchronization" ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "There is one icon per channel that cancels the wait for synchronism with the channel during simulation." .

ns1:ModoOperacionCancelacionRepositioning a ns1:ModoOperacion ;
    rdfs:label "Canceling repositioning"@en ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "Canceling repositioning."@en .

ns1:ModoOperacionConditionalStop a ns1:ModoOperacion ;
    rdfs:label "Conditional stop during simulation" ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "Option to simulate the external \"conditional stop\" switch. Being this option active, the CNC interrupts the simulation in the blocks where the 'M01\" function is programmed." .

ns1:ModoOperacionEDISIMU a ns1:ModoOperacion ;
    rdfs:label "Tool radius compensation" ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "Activate or cancel tool radius compensation to simulate the program." .

ns1:ModoOperacionMultiplePosicionamiento a ns1:ModoOperacion ;
    ns1:identificador "MULTIPLE MACHINING (·M· MODEL)" ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "Parameters P, Q, R, S, T, U and V are optional parameters that may be used in any type of multiple positioning." .

ns1:ModoOperacionReanudacionEjecucionPrograma a ns1:ModoOperacion ;
    rdfs:label "Resuming the execution of the program"@en ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "Resuming the execution of the program. Once all the axes are repositioned or after canceling repositioning, press [START] to resume program execution. • If tool inspection has ended by repositioning all the axes, when pressing [START], the CNC completes the interrupted path and goes on with the rest of the program. • If tool inspection has ended after canceling the repositioning of the axes, when pressing [START], the axes move from their current position to the end point of the interrupted path and then the CNC goes on with the rest of the program."@en .

ns1:ModoOperacionRepositionamientoHusilloPrincipal a ns1:ModoOperacion ;
    rdfs:label "Repositioning the master spindle"@en ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "Repositioning the master spindle. If the status of the master spindle has changed during the inspection, the softkeys will show the M3, M4, M5 or M19 function to restore. The spindle turning status may be restored either together with the repositioning of the axes or separately. If the spindle was interrupted in a positioning with M19, repositioning will complete that positioning."@en .

ns1:ModoOperacionRepositioningEjes a ns1:ModoOperacion ;
    rdfs:label "Repositioning the axes"@en ;
    ns1:textoExtracto "Repositioning the axes. The CNC allows repositioning the axes either one by one or in groups. Use the vertical softkeys to select the axes to be repositioned and press [START]. The CNC will reposition the axes at the selected point (according to the softkey selected earlier) at the feedrate set by the machine manufacturer. Once one axis has reached its position, it will no longer be available."@en .

