ns1:Tabla44 a ns1:Tabla ;
    ns1:textoExtracto """| Instruction. |  | Meaning. |\r
| --- | --- | --- |\r
| $GOTO |  | Block skip. |\r
| $IF $ENDIF\r
$ELSEIF $ELSE |  | Conditional execution. |\r
| $SWITCH $CASE $ENDSWITCH\r
$BREAK $DEFAULT |  | Conditional execution. |\r
| $FOR $ENDFOR\r
$BREAK $CONTINUE |  | Block repetition. |\r
| $WHILE $ENDWHILE\r
$BREAK $CONTINUE |  | Conditional block repetition. |\r
| $DO $ENDDO\r
$BREAK $CONTINUE |  | Conditional block repetition. |\r
| Instruction. | Meaning. |  |\r
| L | Call to a global subroutine. |  |\r
| LL | Call to a local subroutine. |  |\r
| #ABORT | Abort the execution of the program and resume it in another block or program. |  |\r
| #ACS | Fixture coordinate system. |  |\r
| #ANGAX OFF | Turn angular transformation off. |  |\r
| #ANGAX ON | Turn angular transformation on. |  |\r
| #ANGAX SUSP | Freeze angular transformation. |  |\r
| #ASPLINE ENDTANG | Akima splines. Type of final tangent. |  |\r
| #ASPLINE MODE | Akima splines. Selection of tangent type. |  |\r
| #ASPLINE STARTTANG | Akima splines. Type of starting tangent. |  |\r
| #AXIS | Axis upon which the additive manual intervention is applied. |  |\r
| #CALL | Call to a global or local subroutine. |  |\r
| #CALL AX | Add a new axis to the configuration of the channel. |  |\r
| #CALL SP | Add a spindle to the configuration of the channel. |  |\r
| #CAM ON | Activate the electronic cam (real coordinates). |  |\r
| #CAM OFF | Cancel the electronic cam. |  |\r
| #CAX | "C" axis. Activating the spindle as ·C· axis. |  |\r
| #CD OFF | Cancel collision detection. |  |\r
| #CD ON | Activating collision detection. |  |\r
| #CLEAR | Channels. It clears the synchronism marks of the channel. |  |\r
| #CONTJOG | Manual intervention. Feedrate in continuous jog. | \r
| #COMMENT BEGIN | Beginning of comment. |  |\r
| #COMMENT END | End of comment.""" .

